From: Tyagi, Yogesh <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 20 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] intel/compiler/jay: avoid C23 fixed-underlying-type enum

Upstream mesa 26.1.0 declares

    enum jay_predication : uint8_t { ... };

in src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h. The ": uint8_t" syntax is a C23
feature and requires GCC >= 13 (or Clang >= 16). With GCC 11/12 hosts
(e.g. Ubuntu 22.04) and meson's default c_std=c11, this fails to parse,
which cascades into "field has incomplete type" and undeclared
JAY_PREDICATED* identifiers throughout the jay backend.

Drop the fixed underlying type from the enum and change the struct
field to uint8_t so that sizeof(jay_inst) is preserved (the
static_assert below the struct relies on this).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [workaround for older host toolchains]
Signed-off-by: Tyagi, Yogesh <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
---
 src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h b/src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h
--- a/src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h
+++ b/src/intel/compiler/jay/jay_ir.h
@@ -579,7 +579,7 @@ jay_type_is_any_float(enum jay_type t)
    return jay_base_type(t) == JAY_TYPE_F || jay_base_type(t) == JAY_TYPE_BF;
 }
 
-enum jay_predication : uint8_t {
+enum jay_predication {
    /** No predication. */
    JAY_NOT_PREDICATED = 0,
 
@@ -634,7 +634,7 @@ typedef struct jay_inst {
    bool decrement_dep:1;
    unsigned padding  :12;
 
-   enum jay_predication predication;
+   uint8_t predication; /* values from enum jay_predication */
    enum jay_conditional_mod conditional_mod;
 
    jay_def cond_flag; /**< conditional flag */
-- 
2.40.0
